The paper discusses privacy-preserving training of machine learning classifiers using a combination of homomorphic cryptosystem and differential privacy. This topic falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science, including cryptography (cs.CR), machine learning (cs.LG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), cybersecurity (cs.CY), and databases (cs.DB). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CR and cs.LG, followed by cs.DS, cs.CY, and cs.DB.
